 for financial inclusion with a December 2025 MiCA whitepaper filed for Kraken EU/EEA admission representing one of the clearest regulatory compliance pathways of any Southeast Asian payments token, alongside Kraken listing providing regulated fiat on/off ramps across 190+ countries.\n- VELO token utility spans collateral provision, stable asset minting, network fee payment and ecosystem access with 73% of the 24B max supply already in circulation and a tokenomics structure allocating 18% to community development and 16% to strategic reserve for future ecosystem and liquidity management.\n\nIs CP Group institutional backing, Stellar\u2019s proven payment rails, MiCA compliant European exchange listing and a genuine Southeast Asian remittance use case the foundation for VELO\u2019s next chapter or does a 99.6% ATH decline, $58M market cap against 24B circulating tokens at $0.003 and thin $1M daily trading volume suggest the market has assigned near zero value to a payments thesis that has been executing since 2018? \n\nCategory: Payments / DeFi \nCoin Name: $VELO \nCirculating Supply: 17.56B \nMarket Cap: $58.86M \nMarket Cap Rank: #352\nOG (Trust) Score: 38.26\nOG Score Rank: #645\nReviewed by 6 OG Auditors. \n\nSee the full audit, reviews and more on the $VELO Coin page: ogaudit(.)com/crypto/velo-velo\nhttps://t.co/wau9Bt38j7", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 7, "replyCount": 0, "likeCount": 20, "quoteCount": 1, "viewCount": 1411, "createdAt": "Mon May 04 10:16:31 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 2, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2051244572752179254", "displayTextRange": [0, 274], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "OGAudit", "url": "https://x.com/OGAudit", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/OGAudit", "id": "1494810111998636038", "name": "OGAudit\ud83d\udee1\ufe0fCrypto Reviews", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": false, "verifiedType": "Business", "pro